  "time_ut": 1656481101,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0dc4 \u0d9a\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dba\u0da7 \u0da2\u0dbd\u0dba \u0daf\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dc0\u0dca 20 \u0d9a\u0dca \u0dc3\u0d82\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1\u0dba \u0d9a\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dda",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "20 tanks will be developed to supply water to the Maha season",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "20 tanks will be developed soon to supply water for the upcoming Maha season. Of these, 11 tanks have been fully developed to release water and the remaining 9 tanks are in the final stages of development, said Minister Prasanna Ranatunga.",
        "The main objective of developing these tanks is to provide water before providing fertilizer for the Maha season.",
        "This Irrigation Prosperity Tank Development Project is being implemented under the Government's Cultivation War Program to provide an immediate solution to the current food crisis. Under this, 5,000 weedy rural tanks throughout the country will be developed for agricultural purposes.",
        "These facts were revealed during a discussion with officials of the Sri Lanka Land Development Corporation chaired by Urban Development and Housing Minister Prasanna Ranatunga. The discussion was held at the auditorium of the Ministry of Urban Development and Housing yesterday (28).",
        "The first phase of the project was launched in the Badulla, Moneragala and Kurunegala districts. 13 tanks from Badulla, 6 tanks from Moneragala and 1 tank from Kurunegala have been selected for this purpose. It was revealed that nearly 600 acres of paddy lands have been harvested from these tanks.",
        "It is expected to develop 9 tanks on both sides of the Kurunegala and Anuradhapura roads under this irrigation project. The beautification of both the tanks and the road will take place at the same time. The cost for this is 268 million rupees.",
        "In addition, 50 tanks have been identified for development this year. It is estimated that it will cost around Rs. 500 million. It was revealed that 42 additional tanks have been identified from Badulla, 14 from Moneragala and 6 from Kandy for development under this project.",
        "Minister Prasanna Ranatunga pointed out that increasing the existing water capacity is another objective of this irrigation project. The Minister also said that plans have been made to clean the tanks, repair the tank walls, repair the tank sluice and the outlet and plant trees around the tank to protect the rabbit.",
        "Fertilizer, water and other facilities are planned to be provided in parallel to this program. It is also expected to set a fair price for the harvest. The Minister is confident that it will lead to a solution to the agrarian and food crisis. The Minister urged the farmers to resort to this as it is cheaper to start the sale of the harvested rice by the farmers themselves.",
        "Mr. Pradeep Ratnayake, Secretary to the Ministry of Urban Development and Housing, Mr. Hiran Balasuriya, Chairman of the Sri Lanka Land Development Corporation, Mrs. Srimathi Senadheera, General Manager of the Corporation and a number of government officials were present on this occasion."
      ],
